          "username": "kopasiak"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-01-23 16:24:13.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n@Lucjan\nI tried to reproduce your issue but I was unable to do so.\nAre you sure that you have removed:\nglobal:\n  ingress:\n    enabled: false\n\nfrom onap/values and rebuild everything before using the override?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "132c5d3962d7a14c389a7d10b8dc5955dd0e4e70",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2319,
          "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
          "username": "sdesbure"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-01-24 10:35:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n@Lucjan, @krzysztof,\n\nthe priority order should be the following:\n* .values.ingressOverride on the chart\n* .values.global.ingress.enabled in global config\n* .values.ingress.enabled in chart\n\n\nthis gives the following pattern:\n\n| ingress for this chart? | .values.ingressOverride | .values.global.ingress.enabled |  .values.ingress.enabled |\n|-------------------------|-------------------------|--------------------------------|--------------------------|\n|                     yes |                     yes |       whatever (yes/no/absent) | whatever (yes/no/absent) |\n|                      no |                      no |       whatever (yes/no/absent) | whatever (yes/no/absent) |\n|                     yes |                  absent |                            yes | whatever (yes/no/absent) |\n|                      no |                  absent |                             no | whatever (yes/no/absent) |\n|                     yes |                  absent |                         absent |                      yes |\n|                     no  |                  absent |                         absent |                       no |",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "c1ce509f1cb623d13b84becdd53888c9ab7d94e6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4965,
          "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
          "username": "kopasiak"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-01-24 11:03:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nYup and I believe it works this way. The only issue is that in onap/values.yaml we currently have .values.global.ingress.enabled = false so after this patch even if you set .values.ingress.enabled in any of the components it's not going to work and you need to use enabledOverride or remove the global flag and rebuild everything",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "a64c3b1154e76599700c3b725500f7b146f5a396",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2319,
          "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
          "username": "sdesbure"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-01-24 11:05:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nAfter, I do not really see the need of a mix of ingress/not_ingress\nso we may remove the override part no?",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "62e73a7de4318542d4b26964b514442c7cb21ecc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4965,
